phase2.explanation:
The split() failed because a line doesn't have the expected number of commas!

This is a common issue with CSV parsing:
• Empty fields: "value1,,value3" → array has 3 elements (middle is empty)
• Trailing commas: "value1,value2," → array has 3 elements (last is empty)
• Quoted fields with commas: "1,\"Alice, Smith\"" → split breaks!

FIX: Always check array length before accessing:
if (parts.length >= 2) {
    System.out.println(parts[0] + " - " + parts[1]);
} else {
    System.out.println("Invalid line: " + line);
}

For production code, use a proper CSV parser library!

